<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-6197] Get wrong result using XXX Assign operator on byte array</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-6197</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Run this script:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;	byte[] b = new byte&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
	b&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;0&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; = 16&lt;br/&gt;
	b&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;0&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; |= 2&lt;br/&gt;
	println b&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;0&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Got result: 16&lt;br/&gt;
Right result is 18&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This bug only occurs when using xxx Assign operator, e.g. |=, += , -=.&lt;br/&gt;
And Int array works fine.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Groovy lib 2.1.3&lt;br/&gt;
jdk 1.7</environment>
